Module com.example.samplesalad
Package com.example.samplesalad.model

Class Effect

java.lang.Object
com.example.samplesalad.model.Effect
public class Effect extends Object
The Effect class represents an audio effect that can be applied to a Sample.

Each effect has a type (e.g., "Reverb", "Delay") and a set of parameters that configure how the effect is applied.

    • apply

      public void apply(Sample sample)
      Applies the effect to a Sample.

      This method simulates the application of the effect to the sample. In a real implementation, it would adjust the sample's properties based on the effect type and parameters.

      Parameters:
      sample - the Sample to which the effect is applied
